# Releasing

Releasing a new version of `{{ project_name }}` involves tagging a commit, reviewing a draft release, and publishing it — the PyPI upload happens automatically.

## Prerequisites

Before your first release, complete the [PyPI Publishing setup](https://matagus.github.io/django-app-starter/setup/pypi-publishing/).

## Release Steps

### 1. Make sure main is ready

Ensure all changes are merged to `main` and the CI workflow is green.

### 2. Tag the commit

```bash
git tag v0.1.0
```

Use [semantic versioning](https://semver.org/): `v<major>.<minor>.<patch>`.

### 3. Push the tag

```bash
git push origin v0.1.0
```

### 4. Review the draft release

The `release.yml` workflow creates a **draft release** automatically. Go to **Releases** in your GitHub repository, open the draft, review the auto-generated release notes, and make any edits.

### 5. Publish the release

Click **Publish release**.

### 6. PyPI upload runs automatically

Publishing triggers the `publish.yml` workflow, which builds the package with `hatch build` and uploads it to PyPI. Monitor progress in the **Actions** tab.

Once complete, the new version is available at:

```
https://pypi.org/project/{{ project_name }}/
```

## Verifying

```bash
pip install {{ project_name }}==0.1.0
```
